title: 26-gitlogs-diagrams index lifecycle
---
%% Diagram type: flowchart TD
%% What this answers: "How does the §26 maintainer review the diagram index
%%   and tracker? Walk: trigger -> enumerate child specs/issues -> triage
%%   each (new/open/resolved) -> update 99-consistency-report.md -> done."
%% Authoritative source: spec/26-gitlogs-diagrams/00-overview.md + 99-consistency-report.md
%% Audience: §26 maintainers performing periodic index/tracker reviews.
%% Entry point: read 00-overview.md "Index review cadence" section first; this
%%   diagram is the canonical lifecycle for that cadence.
flowchart TD
    Start([Trigger: index/tracker review])
    List[Enumerate child specs / open issues]
    Triage{Item state?}
    Open[Mark as Open + assign owner]
    Closed[Mark as Closed + link resolution]
    Report[Update 99-consistency-report.md]
    Done([End])

    Start --> List --> Triage
    Triage -- new --> Open --> Report
    Triage -- resolved --> Closed --> Report
    Report --> Done
